solution.p:
We use the definition of absolute value to write

        f(x) =
        \begin{cases}
        2x-8 \amp  \text{if} ~~2x-8\ge 0\\
        -(2x-8)  \amp  \text{if} ~~2x-8\lt 0
        \end{cases}

    Then we simplify each expression.

        f(x) =
        \begin{cases}
        2x-8 \amp  \text{if} ~~x\ge 4\\
        8-2x  \amp  \text{if} ~~x\lt 4
        \end{cases}
